product_name: Anastasia Beverly HillsBrow Wiz Precision Eyebrow Pencil Mini
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeThe Anastasia Beverly Hills Deluxe Mini Brow Wiz, an ultra-slim, retractable pencil with the perfect blend of wax and color for outlining and detailing brows with precision and payoff.
details: DetailsFeaturesIdeal for outlining and adding precise detailThe fine-tipped pencil mimics the look of brow hair with detail and precisionFormula features the perfect blend of wax and color that delivers high payoffAdds natural-looking texture to browsBlend with a spoolie brush for a natural-looking finishAvailable in 12 shadesBenefitsCruelty-freeShadesBlonde - For Blonde hair with warm/gold undertonesTaupe - For Blonde hair with cool/ash undertonesAuburn - For Red hair with a dark undertoneCaramel - For Red hair with a light undertoneStrawburn - For light red hair with a warm undertoneDark Brown - For Dark Brown hair with a warm undertoneChocolate - For Medium Brown hair with warm/gold undertonesSoft Brown - For Light Brown hair with warm/cool undertonesAsh Brown - For grey hair with cool/ash undertonesEbony - For Black hair with a warm undertoneMedium Brown - For Medium Brown hair with cool/ash undertonesGranite - For Black hair with a cool undertoneItem 2618209How To UseHOW TO APPLYStart by outlining the under arch of the brow, moving toward the tail end, then blend using a spoolie brush. Outline the upper arch and blend using a spoolie brush. To add detail and dimension, add hairlike strokes to the front of the brow. With the tip of the pencil, lightly sketch in the same direction as the hair's natural growth. Use this technique on sparse areas throughout the brow and blend using a spoolie brush for a natural finish. Remember that all ABH products are highly pigmented, so little pressure is required when applying.PRO TIPS路When preparing to fill in the brow, use Brow Wiz in a shade lighter than your natural hair color to map out the three points of the Golden Ratio along the brow to serve as guide points.路When detailing the brow, always apply Brow Wiz in the same direction as the hair's natural growth. Use light pressure when applying.路To achieve the hair-stroke technique, hold Brow Wiz at a slant, lightly place the tip of the pencil onto the brow area, apply pressure at the bottom and then flick your wrist. This creates a follicle effect at the base.路Layer different shades of ABH brow products to create natural-looking multidimensional brows. First, fill in the brow with a lighter shade of Brow Powder Duo using Brush 7B. Then, detail the brow with tiny hairlike strokes using a darker shade of Brow Wiz.路For a quick application, first outline the shape of the brow (top and bottom), then blend the product through the brow using a spoolie brush. Warm up the fine-tipped pencil on the back of your hand; this allows for a creamy application. Use the hair-stroke technique to complete the brow look.IngredientsHydrogenated Soybean Oil, Hydrogenated Coco-Glycerides, Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil, Zinc Stearate, Copernicia Cerifera (Carnauba) Wax/Cera Carnauba/Cire De Carnauba, Stearic Acid, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Tocopheryl Acetate, Caprylyl Glycol, Phenoxyethanol, Hexylene Glycol, May Contain/Peut Contenir (+/-): Mica, Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891)Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: HOW TO APPLYStart by outlining the under arch of the brow, moving toward the tail end, then blend using a spoolie brush. Outline the upper arch and blend using a spoolie brush. To add detail and dimension, add hairlike strokes to the front of the brow. With the tip of the pencil, lightly sketch in the same direction as the hair's natural growth. Use this technique on sparse areas throughout the brow and blend using a spoolie brush for a natural finish. Remember that all ABH products are highly pigmented, so little pressure is required when applying.PRO TIPS路When preparing to fill in the brow, use Brow Wiz in a shade lighter than your natural hair color to map out the three points of the Golden Ratio along the brow to serve as guide points.路When detailing the brow, always apply Brow Wiz in the same direction as the hair's natural growth. Use light pressure when applying.路To achieve the hair-stroke technique, hold Brow Wiz at a slant, lightly place the tip of the pencil onto the brow area, apply pressure at the bottom and then flick your wrist. This creates a follicle effect at the base.路Layer different shades of ABH brow products to create natural-looking multidimensional brows. First, fill in the brow with a lighter shade of Brow Powder Duo using Brush 7B. Then, detail the brow with tiny hairlike strokes using a darker shade of Brow Wiz.路For a quick application, first outline the shape of the brow (top and bottom), then blend the product through the brow using a spoolie brush. Warm up the fine-tipped pencil on the back of your hand; this allows for a creamy application. Use the hair-stroke technique to complete the brow look.

reviews.headline: Great product!
reviews.comments: Product is of good quality and does what it is designed to do.

reviews.headline: Natural-looking eyebrows!
reviews.comments: This is one of the best eyebrow pencils I have tried. Very easy to use & looks so natural--good color match for me!

reviews.headline: Nice
reviews.comments: Good

reviews.headline: Mini eyebrow pencil defect
reviews.comments: I like mini eyebrow pencil natural look for filling in my eyebrows. I also like that it is cost effective. However, I don't like that I can only use for a week or less;then I have to purchase several pencils since it breaks easily. I try not to press down very hard when using. Can you offer a suggestion for extending pencil life?

reviews.headline: Nice
reviews.comments: I use these brow pencils all the time. The mini size is great for traveling.

reviews.headline: I love it
reviews.comments: I've been using this brow prncil for over six months. It stays on all day and looks great.

reviews.headline: Easy application and I love the small size
reviews.comments: The thin pencil does a good job of mimicking hair.  It's great that the pencil rolls up instead of having to sharpen it.  I bought two colors close to my hair color and like both of them.  Great for travel if you have very limited space.  I have dishwater blond hair and bought the blond and taupe colors.

reviews.headline: Brush breaks off!
reviews.comments: I love the precision I get from this pencil, but the brush end ALWAYS breaks off early on, way before I am finished with the pencil end. I always have to end up using a separate brush. Other than that, its great. ABH, please make a more durable brush end!

reviews.headline: Hate that I love
reviews.comments: Let me start by saying I LOVE this product! That being said, the last four i have purchased have literally lasted like two weeks becayse theu keep crumbling/breaking apart. At thus price point its getting REALLY old and I dont know that I can justify continuing to purchase.

reviews.headline: Love this eyebrow pencil
reviews.comments: I've been using this for a few years and really like it

reviews.headline: What happened to the quality?!
reviews.comments: Fabulous color, good formula, but my gosh the quality of the pencil has gone WAY down. The last three I've purchased have broken and I can no longer use the spooly on the other end. Now I need two products instead of one, completely defeating the purchase. Please, PLEASE, go back to the old product.

reviews.headline: One of my faves
reviews.comments: This product helps make my brows look so good!

reviews.headline: My favorite Eyebrow pencil!
reviews.comments: Love Anastasia eye brow pencil. I make perfect eyebrows!

reviews.headline: Happy!
reviews.comments: I got this because of its high ratings. I am beyond satisfied with this eyebrow pencil! It is very easy to use and it looks natural. I will be buying it again.

reviews.headline: It's ok
reviews.comments: I should have gotten the darker color , it was a little to expensive for me!

reviews.headline: Precision!
reviews.comments: Honestly started using more makeup late in life. Used a few brow pencils before finding this one and I'm so happy with it! Very precise, great color tone match.

reviews.headline: Used to be amazing
reviews.comments: I've used Brow Wiz for years (probably decades) and I've always loved it! It's been my go-to. But the last 3 have had the same issue: the brush end breaks off almost immediately. The first time, I thought maybe I was too rough. The second time, I figured it was a fluke. But now, after the third time, it's clearly a quality issue with the packaging. I hope the issue is addressed - until then, I need to find an alternative.

reviews.headline: Love
reviews.comments: Love

reviews.headline: Holy grail - on my third repurchase
reviews.comments: This may be the single best makeup product I've ever used. So worth the price. It's a perfect color match (which I've never found before). Foolproof to use, don't need additional tools. Looks very natural so I can wear with no other makeup or a full face. On my third - it would be higher but they last forever!

reviews.headline: Never going back
reviews.comments: I keep trying to try other brow products and I keep coming back to this one! Tried and true brow pencil. It never disappoints.

faceoff_negative.comments: The pencil and spool work well when they stay intact. I've had to request a replacement Brow Whiz twice in three months because the plastic is so flimsy that the ends of pencil and spool fall loose. And now the third time in six months it is happening again. I am not rough with it. The Brow Whiz just stays in my makeup pouch. It clearly cannot withstand being transported within the makeup pouch. More durable material should really be considered to make this product worth the money. It's not fair for me to keep replacing this when there is still so much pencil left but I physically cannot maneuver it.
faceoff_negative.headline: Potential to be great product but cheap material
